.TH hsh 1 "December 9th, 2021" "Simple Shell" "hsh General Commands Manual"

.SH NAME
.B
hsh
- a simple version of the GNU command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #cisfun($)
.RB {| COMMAND |}
.RB [| OPTIONS |]
.RB [| ARGUMENTS |]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
shows a
.I prompt line
and waits for the user to write a command and executes it. In
.I interactive mode
this process repeats until the user writes the command
.I 'exit'
. In the
.I non-interactive mode
the command entered is executed once, then the whole process stops and the
.I prompt line
doesn't appear again.

.SH COMMAND
Any of the UNIX commands or any other that executes a command.

.SH OPTIONS
Options vary depending on the
.I COMMAND
entered.

.SH ARGUMENTS
As
.I OPTIONS,
.I ARGUMENTS
will depend on the option entered.

.SH EXAMPLES
In interactive mode:
.B ./hsh
.br
in non-interactive mode:
.B echo "ls -la /tmp" | ./hsh

.SH RETURN VALUE
0 if success, otherwise the exit value

